(4k + 3) ^2 - (4k + 3)
4
\begin{align*} (4k+3)^2-(4k+3)&=16k^2+24k+9-4k-3\\ &=16k^2+20k+6\\ &=4\left(4k^2+5k+1\right)+2\;, \end{align*}
4
(4k + 3)^2 - (4k + 3) = (4k + 3)(4k + 3-1) = (4k + 3)(4k + 2)=2(4k + 3)(2k + 1)
(4k+3)^2-(4k+3)=(4k+3)\{(4k+3)-1\}=(4k+3)(4k+2)
4k+3=2(2k+1)+1
4k+2=2(2k+1)\not\equiv0\pmod4
